<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 RB005 Week 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Greybox It — Find the Fun First · <strong>Course:</strong> Dream Game Studio · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week you build your WHOLE map with plain gray parts. This is called <strong>greyboxing</strong> — find the fun first, decorate later.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each question. Circle or write your answer.</p>
<p><strong>Should you decorate your map BEFORE you know the game is fun? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Your greybox map is all gray, but you can play it from start to goal. Is that OK for this week? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows a good plan first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the problem.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — Every map needs a goal.</p>
<pre><code># good
START → bridge → jumps → GOAL flag
</code></pre>
<pre><code># broken
START → bridge → jumps → ???
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is missing? How does the player win?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — Greybox first, decorate later.</p>
<pre><code># good
Whole map built with plain gray parts.
Colors come later.
</code></pre>
<pre><code># too early
3 days spent painting the start area.
No goal built yet.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong with painting for 3 days first?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code>First build the whole map with plain ____ parts.
Find the fun. Decorate later.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>gray</code> · <code>gold</code> · <code>rainbow</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now open Roblox Studio and greybox your whole map — start, path, goal — all in plain gray parts. Playtest it for 10 minutes. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your greybox map, then explain what you found. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My map starts at … and the goal is …</p>
<p>The fun part was …</p>
<p>The boring part was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you walk through your greybox map. Talk like a tour guide. Try to use these words: <strong>greybox</strong>, <strong>start</strong>, <strong>goal</strong>, <strong>playtest</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Walk from the start to the goal like a player.</li>
<li>Point at the goal and say how you win.</li>
<li>Say one thing you will fix before decorating.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
